```json
{
  "application": "Snakemake",
  "software": [
    "Python 3.9",
    "Snakemake 7.32.3",
    "Singularity 3.10.5",
    "Slurm (if RUNMODE is 'slurm')"
  ],
  "resources": [
    "config/config.yaml",
    "config/fqscreen_config.conf",
    "config/multiqc_config.yaml",
    "config/cluster.yaml",
    "config/tools.yaml",
    "manifest/sample_manifest.csv",
    "workflow/scripts",
    "workflow/Snakefile"
  ],
  "dependencies": [
    "curl (for gathering cluster stats)"
  ]
}
```

This script runs Snakemake, a workflow management system. It requires Python 3.9, Snakemake 7.32.3, and Singularity 3.10.5. If RUNMODE is 'slurm', it also uses Slurm for job scheduling. The script uses several configuration files, a sample manifest, and scripts within the 'workflow' folder. It also requires the curl tool for gathering cluster statistics.
